If the father did not leave a will, his assets will be distributed according to the provisions of the Inheritance Law, which prioritizes the distribution of assets to the following individuals in the following order:

1. The spouse and children of the deceased;
2. The parents of the deceased;
3. The siblings of the deceased;
4. The grandparents of the deceased;
5. Other relatives and creditors of the deceased.

Therefore, if the father's parents (the grandparents) are not mentioned in the will, they will not be entitled to inherit his assets. However, if the father's siblings or other relatives are also not mentioned in the will, the grandparents may have a claim to the assets as distant relatives.

